@ShreySinha02 For an account to be able to review translations, it must first have the rights to do so in a certain language. Assigning the permissions to an account is done by an account with a "Translation Admin" role. To add that role to the admin account (on your local dev environment), go to Admin Page, then under the Roles tab, type in the account username, click the pencil icon, and finally add a new role. 

To assign the review translation rights to an account, go to `/contributor-dashboard-admin` page and under the heading "Add contributor rights", type in the account username, select REVIEW_TRANSLATIONS rights and choose a language that the account can review translations in.

Next, you must have translation data to represent the translations to work with. Follow the instructions [here](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributor-dashboard#local-development). If running the script doesn't work, see the google doc linked in that section that gives instructions for populating translation opportunities.

